Class TimeTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.TimeTable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class TimeTable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is responsible for managing all the index numbers that a particular Student object is registered or in the wait list for.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • registerForCourse

        public void registerForCourse​(java.lang.String courseCodeToBeAdded,
                              IndexNumber indexNumberToBeAdded)
                       throws CourseRegisteredException,
                              ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                              NoVacancyException,
                              CourseInWaitListException,
                              ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                              MaxAuExceededException
        A method that registers the student for a specific course and index number and sends an email to notify the student if he/she has been successfully registered for the course.
        Parameters:
        courseCodeToBeAdded - course code of the course to be registered for.
        indexNumberToBeAdded - IndexNumber object that is to be registered for.
        Throws:
        CourseRegisteredException - if the course selected is already registered.
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the index number that has been selected clashes with the current courses that have been registered already.
        NoVacancyException - if the index of the course selected does not have vacancy.
        CourseInWaitListException - if the course selected is already added to the wait list.
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the index number of the course that have been selected clashes with the timetable of the courses that have already been wait listed for.
        MaxAuExceededException - throws exception when user is still trying to add course when he/she already has reached the maximum AU allowable.
        See Also:
        IndexNumber

      • swapIndexNumberWithPeer

        public void swapIndexNumberWithPeer​(java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped,
                                    Student peer)
                             throws ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                    SameIndexNumberSwapException,
                                    ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                                    PeerClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                    PeerClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        This method performs the swapping of an index number with a peer when all conditions are met.
        Parameters:
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - course code of the course to be swapped with peer.
        peer - Student object that the current user will be swapping index with.
        Throws:
        SameIndexNumberSwapException - if the student and the peer has the same index number.
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the peer's index number clashes with an index number that is in the student's wait list.
        PeerClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the student's index number clashes with an index number that is in the peer's registered list.
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the peer's index number clashes with an index number that is in the student's registered list.
        PeerClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the student's index number clashes with an index number that is in the peer's wait list.

      • swapIndexNumber

        public void swapIndexNumber​(java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped,
                            IndexNumber newIndexNumber)
                     throws ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                            NoVacancySwapException,
                            SameIndexNumberSwapException,
                            ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        Swap index number for a course that the student is registered for.
        Parameters:
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - The course code of the course for which the index number will swapped for the student.
        newIndexNumber - The IndexNumber object that represents the new index number that the student wants to swap to.
        Throws:
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be swapped clashes with a registered index number of the student.
        NoVacancySwapException - if the new index number to be swapped has no vacancies.
        SameIndexNumberSwapException - if the new index number is the same as current index number of the student.
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be swapped clashes with an index number that is in the wait list of the student.

      • dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList

        public void dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList​(Course course,
                                                       IndexNumber indexNumberToBeDropped)
                                                throws CourseInWaitListException,
                                                       ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                                       CourseRegisteredException,
                                                       NoVacancyException,
                                                       ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                                                       MaxAuExceededException
        Contains the logic to drop a course and the index number and register the next student in the wait list for that index number. The exceptions can be ignored since the exceptions should have been taken care of when the index number is * added into the next student in line's wait list.
        Parameters:
        course - The Course object that is to be dropped.
        indexNumberToBeDropped - The IndexNumber object of the index number which the student wants to drop.
        Throws:
        CourseInWaitListException
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException
        CourseRegisteredException
        NoVacancyException
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        MaxAuExceededException
